Lakachaka - - This is our famous camp at the mouth of the Río Aguilani on extensive ancient agriculture terraces, where are two foot bridges. Collections made following the Río Miguillas upriver from the footbridge about 1 km until the canyon becomes impassable 20 km N. of Choquetanga. Semi-deciduous, diverse, riverine forest with various Mimosoid legume forests on the slopes and cliffs. Trees festooned with a rare Floribundia usneiodes.

Mikailpurhua - - If one follows the trail from Laka Chaka at the mouth of the Río Aguilani on the way to Khora, about 4 hours on foot (3.5 km crow flies) to the NNE one crosses two rivers. The north fork is the Río Aguada, the south fork is the Mikhailpurhua 24 km N. of Choquetanga. Very diverse riverine forest with everything from Sorocea to Boehmeria. Semi ever-green.
